# Data Flow and Validation

Database data flow must stay on the server, use typed Zod validation, and route database work through query helpers.

- Retrieve database data in server components by calling helpers from `src/db/queries`.
- Perform database inserts, updates, and deletes in server actions by validating inputs, then calling helpers from `src/db/queries`.
- Validate all data passed to server actions with Zod before using it.
- Give server action inputs explicit TypeScript types; do not type server action inputs as `FormData`.
- Prefer deriving TypeScript input types from Zod schemas when practical, so runtime validation and static types stay aligned.
